ata-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2526801\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Dez 06, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104dgg1665702783914.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/dgg1665702783914.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/dgg1665702783914.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"dgg1665702783914\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                 \n Uniface 10: Changes in Properties\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"dgg1665702783914__unifacechanges_in_properties_6742\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The Properties Inspector of the Uniface IDE enables you to view all the properties of an object at a glance.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"dgg1665702783914__p_d2441e1_d2442e1_d2443e1\">To ensure that the names of properties are consistent and their purpose clear, a number of properties have been renamed, merged, or split.</p>\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"dgg1665702783914__fig_d2444e1_d2445e1_d2446e1\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 1. </span>Properties Inspector</figcaption>\n<img alt=\"Properties Inspector \" aria-label=\"Open image in gallery mode\" class=\"image expandable\" data-fancy=\"gallery\" data-gallery=\"gallery\" data-remote=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/propertiesinspector.png?_LANG=enus\" data-title=\"Figure 1. Properties Inspector\" height=\"582\" role=\"button\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/propertiesinspector.png?_LANG=enus\" style=\"cursor: pointer;\" tabindex=\"0\" width=\"220\"/>\n</figure>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"3\" id=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">New and Changed Properties</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1__entry__1\">\n Old Property\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1__entry__2\">\n New/Changed Property\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1__entry__3\">\n Description\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" colspan=\"3\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1__entry__1 dgg1665702783914__table_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1__entry__2 dgg1665702783914__table_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1__entry__3\">\n                     Common properties:\n                  </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1__entry__1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Description</span>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1__entry__2\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xrw1665702585620.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xrw1665702585620.html\" title=\"Use this property to briefly describe the development object in up to 256 Unicode characters.\">Description</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1__entry__3\">\n This property now supports Unicode, and the length has been increased from 25 to 256 characters (C25 to W256).\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1__entry__1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Comments</span>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1__entry__2\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ipc1665702585697.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ipc1665702585697.html\" title=\"Use this property to provide comments or instructions for the selected development object. You can use the toolbar and standard Windows keyboard shortcuts to format the text, copy and paste, and undo and redo edits.\">Documentation</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1__entry__3\">\n Except for modeled properties and global objects, the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Comments</span> property has been changed to the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Documentation</span> property. It supports RTF and HTML, enabling you to create complete and extensive documentation about each development object.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1__entry__1\">\n —\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1__entry__2\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"uaj1665702714384.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/uaj1665702714384.html\" title=\"This property determines the purpose of the object during development. It is used to separate application objects from templates and palettes.\">Purpose</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1__entry__3\">\n This property applies only to main development objects. It determines whether the object is a palette (a collection of templates), template, or normal development object. Palettes and templates are visible in the Resource Browser.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1__entry__1\">\n —\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1__entry__2\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"cvv1665702762433.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cvv1665702762433.html\" title=\"This property defines a descriptive name for a palette. This name is displayed in the Resource Browser instead of the object name. It can contain up to 256 Unicode characters.\">Alternative Name</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1__entry__3\">\n This property enables you to define a descriptive name for a palette when it is displayed in the Resource Browser. It should preferably be unique but this is not enforced. If not defined, the literal object name is shown.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" colspan=\"3\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1__entry__1 dgg1665702783914__table_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1__entry__2 dgg1665702783914__table_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1__entry__3\">\n                     Component Properties\n                  </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1__entry__1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Keep Data in Memory</span>\n<p class=\"p\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Drop Component from Memory</span>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1__entry__2\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ypq1665702689055.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ypq1665702689055.html\" title=\"Specifies whether the component definition is cached in memory.\">Component Behavior</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1__entry__3\">\n Specifies whether the component definition is cached in memory.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1__entry__1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Behavior</span>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1__entry__2\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qsg1665702688984.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qsg1665702688984.html\" title=\"Determines the degree to which data in the component can be edited and stored.\">Data Access</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">The property has been renamed for clarity.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1__entry__1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Overlay Previous Form</span>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1__entry__2\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Is Independent Form</span>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1__entry__3\">The property has been renamed and the default\n                     value is <code class=\"ph codeph\">true</code> for normal forms and <code class=\"ph codeph\">false</code> for\n                     contained forms. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" colspan=\"3\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1__entry__1 dgg1665702783914__table_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1__entry__2 dgg1665702783914__table_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1__entry__3\">\n                     Entity Properties:\n                  </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1__entry__1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Data Access</span>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1__entry__2\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jlp1665702702609.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jlp1665702702609.html\" title=\"Defines how an entity will access the data store—via a database path, or via an entity service.\">Data Access</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1__entry__3\">\n The property has been renamed and can be explicitly set.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1__entry__1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">DBMS Path</span>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1__entry__2\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"cyp1665702702678.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cyp1665702702678.html\" title=\"DBMS path to use when storing occurrences of this entity. This is a named route to the Uniface DBMS connector used to connect to the database. Valid values are Uniface default paths ($DEF, $SYS, $UUU), supported databases and file formats, and user-defined paths. The default is DEF.\">Database Path</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1__entry__3\">The property has been renamed and the value\n                        <code class=\"ph codeph\">Not in Database</code> is now set using the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Database\n                        Behavior</span> property. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1__entry__1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Database Behavior</span>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1__entry__2\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"mcg1665702702535.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mcg1665702702535.html\" title=\"Determines whether the entity is stored in a database. If N, the Data Access and Database Path property values are ignored.\">Database Behavior</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1__entry__3\">\n It is not possible to override the value of this property for a Subtype Entity.\n <p class=\"p\">During migration, any subtype entity that has this property set to <code class=\"ph codeph\">F</code> when its supertype is <code class=\"ph codeph\">T</code>, with have <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Database Behavior</span> set to <code class=\"ph codeph\">\"\"</code> (Inherited) and <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Database Access</span> set to <code class=\"ph codeph\">N</code> (None).</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1__entry__1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Entity Interface</span>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1__entry__2\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"enu1665702584272.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/enu1665702584272.html\" title=\"This property (also known as the entity interface) determines how the data is mapped to the database.\">Database Interface (Entities)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1__entry__3\">\n Specifies how the data interfaces with the database, including the data type and length.\n <p class=\"p\">Several properties have been merged into one property, so that you can specify either a shorthand code or a reference to a Modeled Entity Interface.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1__entry__1\">\n —\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1__entry__2\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"tbr1665702589761.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/tbr1665702589761.html\" title=\"Causes occurrences retrieved from the server to be incrementally rendered in a dynamic server page using the specified batch sizes.\">RenderingIncrement</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1__entry__3\">\n Entity property that can be set in ProcScript or JavaScript to control incremental rendering in dynamic server pages.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" colspan=\"3\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1__entry__1 dgg1665702783914__table_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1__entry__2 dgg1665702783914__table_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1__entry__3\">\n                     Field Properties:\n                  </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1__entry__1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Characteristics</span>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1__entry__2\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"pta1665702586322.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/pta1665702586322.html\" title=\"Determines whether the Field's data can be externalized outside the component, either by storing it in a database or passing it in an entity or occurrence parameter.\">Is External</a>\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"iri1665702586413.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/iri1665702586413.html\" title=\"Determines whether the field contents are same for all occurrences of the entity.\">Is Static</a>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"oji1665702586488.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/oji1665702586488.html\" title=\"Determines whether the field is a control field in a form component, meaning that it can be selected with the mouse but not get focus. This affects validation behavior.\">Is Control</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">The values of the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Characteristics</span> property have been split over several new properties that more accurately reflect the behavior.</p>\n<p class=\"p\">See the property descriptions for details.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1__entry__1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Field Interface</span>\n<p class=\"p\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Field Interface Shorthand</span>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Field Interface Template</span>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"enu1665702584272.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/enu1665702584272.html\" title=\"This property (also known as the entity interface) determines how the data is mapped to the database.\">Database Interface (Entities)</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">Specifies how the data interfaces with the database, including the data type and length.</p>\n<p class=\"p\">Several properties have been merged into one property, so that you can specify either a shorthand code or a reference to a Modeled Field Interface.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1__entry__1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Field Syntax Shorthand</span>\n<p class=\"p\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Field Syntax Template</span>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1__entry__2\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zlt1665702557043.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zlt1665702557043.html\" title=\"The Field Syntax property specifies the input format for data, including the entry format (for example, 1-Dec-14 or 20141201), the allowed characters, and whether the field is mandatory or read-only.\">Field Syntax</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">You can specify either a shorthand code or a reference to a Modeled Field Syntax.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1__entry__1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Field Layout Shorthand</span>\n<p class=\"p\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Field Layout Template</span>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1__entry__2\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"lpv1665702557117.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lpv1665702557117.html\" title=\"Property that specifies how the field's data is formatted for display. The value can be a comma-separated list of shorthand codes, or a reference to a modeled field layout.\">Field Layout</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">You can specify either a shorthand code or a reference to a Modeled Field Layout.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"dgg1665702783914__p_d2450e1_d2451e1_d2452e1\">Only the display names of the following properties have changed. Their behavior remains the same.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d83e1_d84e1_d85e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 2. </span><span class=\"title\">Changed Property Names</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d83e1_d84e1_d85e1__entry__1\">\n Old Property Name\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d83e1_d84e1_d85e1__entry__2\">\n New Property Name\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d83e1_d84e1_d85e1__entry__1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Border</span>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d83e1_d84e1_d85e1__entry__2\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rmo1665702689618.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rmo1665702689618.html\" title=\"Determines whether a rectangular border is displayed around the form component's outer edge in character mode.\">Borderline</a>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d83e1_d84e1_d85e1__entry__1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Clear Area</span>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d83e1_d84e1_d85e1__entry__2\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"lma1665702689548.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lma1665702689548.html\" title=\"Determines whether the screen is cleared before and after running a form that runs another form. Applicable only when the form is run in character mode. True or False (Default).\">Clear?</a>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d83e1_d84e1_d85e1__entry__1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Header Depth</span>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d83e1_d84e1_d85e1__entry__2\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fel1665702689477.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fel1665702689477.html\" title=\"Number of header lines displayed at the top of the component in character mode. The remainder of the form is scrolled. No default.\">Header Length</a>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d83e1_d84e1_d85e1__entry__1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Read Translation Table</span>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d83e1_d84e1_d85e1__entry__2\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"iku1665702689266.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/iku1665702689266.html\" title=\"Name of the Keyboard Translation Table used to interpret field data upon input.\">Input Translation</a>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d83e1_d84e1_d85e1__entry__1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Write Translation Table</span>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d83e1_d84e1_d85e1__entry__2\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"dbe1665702689335.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dbe1665702689335.html\" title=\"Name of the Keyboard Translation Table used to convert field data upon output.\">Output Translation</a>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d83e1_d84e1_d85e1__entry__1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Overlay Parent</span>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dgg1665702783914__table_d83e1_d84e1_d85e1__entry__2\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"lsu1665702783988.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lsu1665702783988.html\" title=\"Name of form instance that the current form will overlay. This ensures that the current form is only displayed over the specified parent, and disappears when focus is switches to another form instance. This property can only be set if the current form is a Contained Form or if the property Is Independent Form is false.\">Parent Form (TABPAGE)</a>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526801\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526801\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Uniface 10: Changes in Properties Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Dez 06, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Uniface 10: Changes in Properties The Properties Inspector of the Uniface IDE enables you to view all the properties of an object at a glance. To ensure that the names of properties are consistent and their purpose clear, a number of properties have been renamed, merged, or split. Figure 1. Properties Inspector Table 1. New and Changed Properties Old Property New/Changed Property Description Common properties: Description Description This property now supports Unicode, and the length has been increased from 25 to 256 characters (C25 to W256). Comments Documentation Except for modeled properties and global objects, the Comments property has been changed to the Documentation property. It supports RTF and HTML, enabling you to create complete and extensive documentation about each development object. — Purpose This property applies only to main development objects. It determines whether the object is a palette (a collection of templates), template, or normal development object. Palettes and templates are visible in the Resource Browser. — Alternative Name This property enables you to define a descriptive name for a palette when it is displayed in the Resource Browser. It should preferably be unique but this is not enforced. If not defined, the literal object name is shown. Component Properties Keep Data in Memory Drop Component from Memory Component Behavior Specifies whether the component definition is cached in memory. Behavior Data Access The property has been renamed for clarity. Overlay Previous Form Is Independent Form The property has been renamed and the default value is true for normal forms and false for contained forms. Entity Properties: Data Access Data Access The property has been renamed and can be explicitly set. DBMS Path Database Path The property has been renamed and the value Not in Database is now set using the Database Behavior property. Database Behavior Database Behavior It is not possible to override the value of this property for a Subtype Entity. During migration, any subtype entity that has this property set to F when its supertype is T , with have Database Behavior set to \"\" (Inherited) and Database Access set to N (None). Entity Interface Database Interface (Entities) Specifies how the data interfaces with the database, including the data type and length. Several properties have been merged into one property, so that you can specify either a shorthand code or a reference to a Modeled Entity Interface. — RenderingIncrement Entity property that can be set in ProcScript or JavaScript to control incremental rendering in dynamic server pages. Field Properties: Characteristics Is External Is Static Is Control The values of the Characteristics property have been split over several new properties that more accurately reflect the behavior. See the property descriptions for details. Field Interface Field Interface Shorthand Field Interface Template Database Interface (Entities) Specifies how the data interfaces with the database, including the data type and length. Several properties have been merged into one property, so that you can specify either a shorthand code or a reference to a Modeled Field Interface. Field Syntax Shorthand Field Syntax Template Field Syntax You can specify either a shorthand code or a reference to a Modeled Field Syntax. Field Layout Shorthand Field Layout Template Field Layout You can specify either a shorthand code or a reference to a Modeled Field Layout. Only the display names of the following properties have changed. Their behavior remains the same. Table 2. Changed Property Names Old Property Name New Property Name Border Borderline Clear Area Clear? Header Depth Header Length Read Translation Table Input Translation Write Translation Table Output Translation Overlay Parent Parent Form (TABPAGE) Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}